<subSubSection id="C35C6569CC659542FEC6FA1CFCA4A7C6" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="57" pageId="1" pageNumber="56" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BF936E2CC659542FEC6FA1CFD6DA5CE" blockId="1.[264,1324,1497,1883]" lastBlockId="2.[264,1325,284,1070]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="57" pageId="1" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis id="B932EAF0CC659541FEC6FA1CFEFBA1BA" box="[264,383,1497,1522]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="56">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Eleven pairs of biserial phyllobranchiate gills. Rostrum triangular or reduced to broadly rounded lobe; lateral projections developed or obsolete. Ocular peduncles stout, corneas prominently dilated or not; ocular acicles triangular, each with small submarginal spine. Antennal peduncle with supernumerary segmentation. Mandible with entirely calcified cutting edge. Maxillule (
<figureCitation id="137D2A67CC659541FD58F9BCFD58A2DB" box="[662,732,1657,1683]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[264,368,1683,1707]" captionTargetBox="[341,1245,345,1633]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[316,1270,326,1657]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Pteropagurus inermis n. sp., a – d, holotype ovig. female (sl = 1.6 mm) (MNHN Pg 7633), e – h, paratype male (sl = 1.3 mm) (MNHN Pg 7634). a, shield and cephalic appendages (aesthetascs omitted); b, sternites of second and third pereopods (thoracic sternites XI &amp; XII) (ventral view); c, left fourth pereopod (lateral view); d, telson; e, right maxillule; f, right maxilla; g, right first maxilliped; h, right third maxilliped. Scales equal 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/171639/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="56">
Fig. 
<number id="3D8E24C5CC659541FD03F9BCFD58A2DB" box="[717,732,1657,1683]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
e) with external lobe of endopod obsolete, internal lobe with 
<number id="3D8E24C5CC659541FE4FF964FE14A2F3" box="[385,400,1697,1723]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56" value="1.0">1</number>
stiff bristle. Maxilla (
<figureCitation id="137D2A67CC659541FD57F964FD64A2F3" box="[665,736,1697,1723]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[264,368,1683,1707]" captionTargetBox="[341,1245,345,1633]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[316,1270,326,1657]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Pteropagurus inermis n. sp., a – d, holotype ovig. female (sl = 1.6 mm) (MNHN Pg 7633), e – h, paratype male (sl = 1.3 mm) (MNHN Pg 7634). a, shield and cephalic appendages (aesthetascs omitted); b, sternites of second and third pereopods (thoracic sternites XI &amp; XII) (ventral view); c, left fourth pereopod (lateral view); d, telson; e, right maxillule; f, right maxilla; g, right first maxilliped; h, right third maxilliped. Scales equal 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/171639/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="56">
Fig. 
<number id="3D8E24C5CC659541FD1CF964FD64A2F3" box="[722,736,1697,1723]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
f) with endopod considerably overreaching distal margin of scaphognathite. First maxilliped (
<figureCitation id="137D2A67CC659541FC8EF90CFC14A2AB" box="[832,912,1737,1763]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[264,368,1683,1707]" captionTargetBox="[341,1245,345,1633]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[316,1270,326,1657]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Pteropagurus inermis n. sp., a – d, holotype ovig. female (sl = 1.6 mm) (MNHN Pg 7633), e – h, paratype male (sl = 1.3 mm) (MNHN Pg 7634). a, shield and cephalic appendages (aesthetascs omitted); b, sternites of second and third pereopods (thoracic sternites XI &amp; XII) (ventral view); c, left fourth pereopod (lateral view); d, telson; e, right maxillule; f, right maxilla; g, right first maxilliped; h, right third maxilliped. Scales equal 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/171639/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="56">
Fig. 
<quantity id="4CBE9B07CC659541FC4FF90CFC14A2AB" box="[897,912,1737,1763]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="56" unit="g" value="2.0">2</quantity>
</figureCitation>
g) with slender exopod. Second maxilliped without distinguishing characters. Third maxilliped (
<figureCitation id="137D2A67CC659541FBE0F934FBF9A343" box="[1070,1149,1777,1803]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[264,368,1683,1707]" captionTargetBox="[341,1245,345,1633]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[316,1270,326,1657]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Pteropagurus inermis n. sp., a – d, holotype ovig. female (sl = 1.6 mm) (MNHN Pg 7633), e – h, paratype male (sl = 1.3 mm) (MNHN Pg 7634). a, shield and cephalic appendages (aesthetascs omitted); b, sternites of second and third pereopods (thoracic sternites XI &amp; XII) (ventral view); c, left fourth pereopod (lateral view); d, telson; e, right maxillule; f, right maxilla; g, right first maxilliped; h, right third maxilliped. Scales equal 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/171639/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="56">
Fig. 
<number id="3D8E24C5CC659541FBA0F934FBF9A343" box="[1134,1149,1777,1803]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
h) with crista dentata reduced, no accessory tooth. Sternite of third (thoracic somite IX of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD74B13CC659541FB49F8DCFAA6A37B" author="Pilgrim" box="[1159,1314,1817,1843]" pageId="1" pageNumber="68" refString="Pilgrim, R. L. C. (1973) Axial skeleton and musculature in the thorax of the hermit crab, Pagurus bernhardus [Anomura: Paguridae]. Journal of the Marine Biological Association United Kingdom, 53, 363 - 396." type="journal article" year="1973">
Pilgrim 
<number id="3D8E24C5CC659541FB28F8DCFAA6A37B" box="[1254,1314,1817,1843]" pageId="1" pageNumber="56" value="1973.0">1973</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) maxillipeds unarmed. Sternite of chelipeds (thoracic somite X) quite narrow, incompletely fused to larger sternite of second pereopods. Sternite of third pereopods (thoracic somite XII) sexually dimorphic (
<figureCitation id="137D2A67CC669542FDFCFE81FDF9A516" box="[562,637,324,350]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[264,368,1683,1707]" captionTargetBox="[341,1245,345,1633]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[316,1270,326,1657]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Pteropagurus inermis n. sp., a – d, holotype ovig. female (sl = 1.6 mm) (MNHN Pg 7633), e – h, paratype male (sl = 1.3 mm) (MNHN Pg 7634). a, shield and cephalic appendages (aesthetascs omitted); b, sternites of second and third pereopods (thoracic sternites XI &amp; XII) (ventral view); c, left fourth pereopod (lateral view); d, telson; e, right maxillule; f, right maxilla; g, right first maxilliped; h, right third maxilliped. Scales equal 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/171639/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">
Figs 
<number id="3D8E24C5CC669542FDA3FE81FDF9A516" box="[621,637,324,350]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
b. 
<number id="3D8E24C5CC669542FD56FE81FD23A516" box="[664,679,324,350]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="3.0">3</number>
b), very broad and prominently produced posteriorly in males, produced little if at all in females.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF936E2CC669542FEF6FE51FA90A5B6" blockId="2.[264,1325,284,1070]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">Chelipeds long, slender, right appreciably stouter, but not necessarily longer. Second pereopods distinctly shorter than third. Fourth pereopods semichelate or minutely chelate, propodal rasp with few scales. Fifth pereopods chelate, rasp moderately well developed.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF936E2CC669542FEF6FDC9FCA4A7C6" blockId="2.[264,1325,284,1070]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">
Males with elongate, stout right sexual tube directed posteriorly and externally and curving up over anterior portion of pleon; very short left sexual tube; uniramous left pleopods 
<number id="3D8E24C5CC669542FEB3FD99FE28A63E" box="[381,428,604,630]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5</number>
. Females with paired gonopores or unpaired left; no paired and modified first pleopods, unpaired biramous left pleopods 
<number id="3D8E24C5CC669542FC98FD41FC00A6D6" box="[854,900,644,670]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4</number>
, pleopod 
<number id="3D8E24C5CC669542FBCEFD41FB8BA6D6" box="[1024,1039,644,670]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="5.0">5</number>
short, uniramous as in males. Pleon somewhat reduced, straight; pleomere 
<number id="3D8E24C5CC669542FC4BFD69FC10A68E" box="[901,916,684,710]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="1.0">1</number>
partially fused with last thoracic somite, tergites of pleomeres 
<number id="3D8E24C5CC669542FDB0FD11FD2EA6A6" box="[638,682,724,750]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="3.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="2.0">2–5</number>
weakly delineated; pleomere 
<number id="3D8E24C5CC669542FBE9FD11FBB2A6A6" box="[1063,1078,724,750]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="6.0">6</number>
chitinous. Uropods symmetrical; protopods each with posteriorly directed spine; exopods elongate, endopods reduced, both with 
<number id="3D8E24C5CC669542FE3BFCE1FD80A776" box="[501,516,804,830]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="1.0">1</number>
or 
<number id="3D8E24C5CC669542FDFCFCE1FDC5A776" box="[562,577,804,830]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="2.0">2</number>
marginal rows of scales. Telson without transverse incisions, with slight median concavity or cleft in terminal midline, terminal margins rounded or oblique, unarmed or with few minute bristles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
